        <definition>size_t NDDimension::offset</definition>
        <argsstring></argsstring>
        <name>offset</name>
        <briefdescription>
<para>The offset relative to the origin of the original data source (detector, for example). </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>If a selected region of the detector is being read, then this value may be &gt; 0. The offset value is specified in unbinned pixels, and in the default orientation, not reversed. The offset value is cumulative, so if a plugin such as <ref refid="class_n_d_plugin_r_o_i" kindref="compound">NDPluginROI</ref> further selects a subregion, the offset is relative to the first element in the detector, and not to the first element of the region passed to <ref refid="class_n_d_plugin_r_o_i" kindref="compound">NDPluginROI</ref>. </para>
        </detaileddescription>
